@startuml DisplayLayoutStateMachine
title Display layout second external toggle state machine

hide empty description

state "Mac input\nextended layout" as MacInput
state "Sending alt-input command\nrepair suppressed" as SwitchingToAlt
state "Alt-input intent\nmirrored layout" as AltInput
state "Sending Mac-input command\nextended layout first" as RestoringToMac

[*] --> MacInput : startup / saved state defaults on

MacInput --> SwitchingToAlt : toggle_second_external
SwitchingToAlt --> AltInput : mirror succeeds\nthen m1ddc alt-input command returns success
SwitchingToAlt --> MacInput : mirror fails\nor m1ddc alt-input command fails\nrollback extended layout

AltInput --> RestoringToMac : toggle_second_external\nor repair_display_layout hotkey
RestoringToMac --> MacInput : extended layout restored\nthen m1ddc Mac-input command returns success
RestoringToMac --> AltInput : m1ddc Mac-input command fails

MacInput --> MacInput : auto repair\napply matching profile
SwitchingToAlt --> SwitchingToAlt : screen change / wake\nskip auto repair
AltInput --> AltInput : screen change / wake\nskip auto repair
RestoringToMac --> RestoringToMac : screen change / wake\nskip auto repair

note right of SwitchingToAlt
Set saved state away from Mac input before mirror.
This prevents the screen watcher from undoing mirror
while the alternate-input command is still in progress.
The physical input may remain unchanged on the home dock/KVM path.
end note

note right of RestoringToMac
Restore extended layout before sending the Mac-input command.
The command is best-effort on dock/KVM paths.
end note

@enduml
